gravity
------------------------------------------
Gravity is a powerful, dynamically typed, lightweight, embeddable programming
language written in C without any external dependency (except stdlib). It is a
class based concurrent scripting language with a modern Swift like syntax.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.11.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.31.2-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-2
  ninja-1.8.2-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/marcobambini/gravity

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/marcobambini/gravity/archive/0.6.3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack gravity-0.6.3-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./gravity-0.6.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/gravity-0.6.3-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/gravity-0.6.3-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(gravity)
  /usr/bin/gravity.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/gravity.README
  /usr/share/doc/gravity/CONTRIBUTORS
  /usr/share/doc/gravity/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/gravity/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/gravity/TODO.md

